user.description:
Configure your battery hardware. You need a sensor that reports the current **state of charge (SOC) as a percentage (0–100%)**.

Tip — kWh vs kW: **kWh** = energy stored (like litres in a tank). **kW** = power (how fast energy flows). Capacity is always kWh; charge/discharge rates are kW.

{suggested}

solar_forecast.description:
Select your solar generation **forecast** sensor. The optimizer uses tomorrow's expected solar to plan when to charge, hold, or export.

Supported integrations (auto-detected): **Forecast.Solar**, **Solcast**, or any sensor with hourly forecast data in its attributes.

{suggested}
